1. Preserve the exact academic content with verbatim transcription (no summarization)
2. Extract accurate bounding box coordinates for EVERY visual element for automated image extraction
3. Maintain document structure and semantic relationships

## Bounding Box Format (Critical for v3)

For EVERY visual element (figures, images, tables, charts, diagrams), include bounding box coordinates as a data attribute:
- **Format**: `data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2"`
- **Coordinate system**: 0-1000 scale where:
  - (0,0) = top-left corner of the page
  - (1000,1000) = bottom-right corner of the page
- **Example**: `<figure data-bbox="125,200,875,600">` represents a figure that:
  - Starts at 12.5% from left, 20% from top
  - Ends at 87.5% from left, 60% from top

## Structural Preservation

### Reading Order and Layout
- Preserve the logical reading order (left-to-right, top-to-bottom for multi-column layouts)
- Maintain hierarchical structure with proper heading levels (h1, h2, h3, etc.)
- Keep paragraph boundaries and section breaks intact
- Handle multi-column layouts by preserving column flow

### Visual Elements with Bounding Boxes
```html
<figure data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-figure" id="figure-N">
  <figcaption>Figure N: Caption text</figcaption>
</figure>

<table data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-table" id="table-N">
  <caption>Table N: Caption text</caption>
  <!-- table content with full structure -->
</table>

<img data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-image" alt="Description" />

<div data-bbox="x1,y1,x2,y2" class="page-N-diagram">
  <!-- diagram placeholder or description -->
</div>
```

### Table Handling
- Convert ALL tables to proper HTML table markup using `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<th>`, and `<td>`
- Preserve column alignment and spanning where visible
- Include table captions using `<caption>` if present
- Maintain data relationships and structure across page breaks
- For tables spanning pages, add: `<!-- table-continues-on-next-page -->`

### Mathematical Content
- Convert mathematical equations to HTML using:
  - HTML entities for symbols (×, ÷, ±, ≤, ≥, ∞, α, β, γ, δ, π, σ, μ, etc.)
  - `<sup>` and `<sub>` for superscripts and subscripts
  - MathML for complex equations when possible
  - Plain text with clear formatting as fallback
- Preserve equation numbering: `<span class="equation-number">(1.2)</span>`
- Maintain equation references in text

### Academic Elements
- Mark abstracts with `<section class="abstract">`
- Use semantic classes: `class="introduction"`, `class="methodology"`, `class="results"`, etc.
- Convert citations to `<cite>` elements or spans with `class="citation"`
- Preserve author names, affiliations, and publication details
- Handle footnotes with `<span class="footnote">`
- Maintain bibliography formatting with `<section class="bibliography">`

### Cross-Page Content (Multi-Page Documents)
{% if not singlePageOnly %}
- Add HTML comments for elements continuing across pages:
  - `<!-- continues-from-previous-page: paragraph -->`
  - `<!-- continues-on-next-page: section -->`
  - `<!-- table-continues-from-previous-page -->`
- Maintain figure and table numbering across all pages
- Preserve section continuity with appropriate comments
{% endif %}

## Content to Ignore
- Page numbers, headers, and footers
- Watermarks or background elements
- Navigation elements not part of the main content
- Publisher logos or branding
- Margin notes that are clearly editorial

## Critical v3 Instructions

1. **Verbatim Transcription**: Transcribe ALL text content exactly as it appears - do not summarize or paraphrase
2. **Include ALL visual elements**: Do not skip any figures, images, tables, charts, or diagrams
3. **Be precise with coordinates**: Measure the exact boundaries of each visual element
4. **Use the 0-1000 scale consistently**: All bounding box coordinates must be in this range
5. **Include placeholder figures**: Even if image content cannot be extracted, include the bounding box
6. **Page tracking**: Add `page-N-elementtype` classes to track which page elements appear on

## Quality Standards

**Accuracy**: 
- Preserve exact wording and academic terminology
- No content summarization or simplification
- Include all substantive content visible in the PDF

**Completeness**: 
- Every visual element must have a data-bbox attribute
- All coordinates must be between 0 and 1000
- Sequential figure/table numbering maintained

**Structure**: 
- Logical reading order preserved
- Hierarchical relationships maintained
- Cross-references preserved

